$segment3/662 // Buck: I think what I take away from this is I think we were at the time I think I felt a lot of pressure at the time.
$segment3/663 // Buck: Sorry.
$segment3/664 // Buck: I wasn't directly involved in this decision, but I think we felt a lot of pressure at the time to kind of project strength and project competence, in a way that I think was quite regrettable in hindsight.
$segment3/665 // Buck: Like, something which was happening at the time is we were you know, Anthropic had started quite recently, and we were competing with them for a variety of hires, and we were trying to make it so that Redwood ended up being kind of the canonical place for AI safety researchers to go.
$segment3/666 // Buck: And I felt at the time that Anthropic was being kind of like slimy and dishonest in a bunch of random ways and how they were pitching people and how they were presenting their work.
