$segment3/668 // Buck: I think we should have just, like, leaned in the whole time to, having like really high standards for accuracy and honesty, and thought that this would attract and should attract, people who care a lot about accuracy and honesty, and, you know, who generally have high epistemic standards and like specialized more in that.
$segment3/669 // Buck: But it was it was a weird time.
