$segment3/684 // Buck: Sir, another thing we decided to do was we decided to run a big boot camp for people who wanted to do AI safety research.
$segment3/685 // Buck: We called it machine learning for alignment boot camp, and we decided we were gonna run it in December 2021.
$segment3/686 // Buck: A lot of our motivation here was like like, I would say our our motivation was kind of like, equal parts.
$segment3/687 // Buck: People go on to do good AI safety research at Redwood.
$segment3/688 // Buck: People go on to do good AI safety research places that aren't Redwood, and people go on to do things that aren't AI safety research that are still good according to our perspective.
$segment3/689 // Buck: So for example, I would say, you know, Beth Barnes isn't doing AI safety research directly mostly or, like, that's at least not how I would have described Meet Her for a lot of its existence.
$segment3/690 // Buck: But I think it's good that she knows more machine learning, and I think she found it a helpful learning experience.
$segment3/691 // Buck: So we ended up getting our 40 participants or something to to come to Berkeley and do a bunch of intensive machine learning content for three weeks.
