$segment3/705 // Ryan: I wouldn't have said there was pressure to, you know, make sure that you can make the money to feed your family exactly, but also wouldn't have said, like, the pressure was in favor of screwing around.
$segment3/706 // Buck: Yeah.
$segment3/707 // Buck: At the very least, I think you ended up yeah, whatever.
$segment3/708 // Buck: I felt like it was this incredibly energetic environment.
$segment3/709 // Buck: And the other thing was, like, a lot of the time when you're learning to program, there's just random stuff that is annoying and you can get stuck on.
$segment3/710 // Buck: And when there's people around you who can get you unstuck, makes it a lot easier to, like, enter these flow states where you just, like, do programming work for, like, many, many hours at a time or just, like, for most of the hours of the day.
$segment3/711 // Buck: And I thought that was a great time, and I wanted to replicate that in this, you know, this cutting this, like, machine machine learning boot camp.
