$segment3/1104 // Ryan: Mhmm.
$segment3/1105 // Ryan: And it's, I think, very easy to be misled where you can say, oh, what's going on is x because you do some causal intervention experiments where you're like, okay, we, like, did some additional amount.
$segment3/1106 // Ryan: We, like, you know, added more of this and that caused that effect, and we added more of that, so we caused that effect.
$segment3/1107 // Ryan: And so you're like, okay, the explanation of how the model computes x is is y.
$segment3/1108 // Ryan: But actually, what you found is that part of how the model computes x is y.
$segment3/1109 // Ryan: And in fact, you're right that that's one of the mechanisms, but it's not necessarily the only mechanism.
