$segment6/403 // Ryan: What do think of the risk that control backfires by preventing warning shots?
$segment6/404 // Buck: I don't feel very bad about this risk.
$segment6/405 // Buck: I mean, one mechanism that a lot of control works through is making it so that you catch the AI when it tries to do bad things.
$segment6/406 // Buck: And I think that putting more work into catching the AI when it tries to do bad things just seems pretty good.
$segment6/407 // Buck: Like, feel like a lot of the cases where control works, like what happens is the control means that instead of the AI trying to do a bad thing and then succeeding in, like, hacking you, or maybe even just, like, failing at hacking you, instead of you never learning about this, you do learn about this.
$segment6/408 // Buck: And then perhaps instead of learning about this a little bit, but then, like, not really thinking about it too much, there's, like, more focus on really drilling down into what happened and whether the AI was failing on purpose, like, whether it was attacking on purpose.
