$segment6/426 // Buck: Like, it's, plausibly plausibly a lot easier for an AI to do things that a company would consider to be like a grave security failure than for the AI to, actually take over the world.
$segment6/427 // Buck: And plausibly, therefore, the first AIs that are able to, for instance, self expatriate or, you know, run themselves rogue inside a data center and, like, take a bunch of actions in the outside world, plausibly, those AIs will have a much better chance of wreaking a moderate amount of havoc than actually being an existential risk to the world.
$segment6/428 // Buck: And plausibly, we should think of that as good news from our perspective.
