$segment6/794 // Buck: I would look for the the best analogies for people inside the US government who had tried to persuade, the government and other governments to treat technologies this way in the past and try to imitate those.
$segment6/795 // Buck: My main objectives would be having more decision makers think of AI as a big deal, a potential source of huge risk.
$segment6/796 // Buck: I would also pay some attention to mitigating risk of US government, like overuse or concentration of power for the AIs.
$segment6/797 // Buck: I I think there might be some methods you can apply to making it less likely that, for instance, the US president ends up getting inappropriate levels of control over the AI.
$segment6/798 // Ryan: Yeah.
$segment6/799 // Ryan: What kind of mid career professionals would you be most excited to see switch to AI safety?
